HEADWORD: Essonite
<hw>Es"so*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named from Gr. <?/
inferior, because not so hard as some minerals it resembles, <it>e.
g.</it>, hyacinth.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Cinnamon stone, a
variety of garnet. See <er>Garnet</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

